## Error logging
use getLogger without f strings to log errors and warnings

###example
        try:
            return self.i2c_bus.read_byte_data(0x69, 0x00) == 0x11
        except (OSError, IOError) as e:
            getLogger().warning("Error reading WittyPi: %s", e)

## Exception handling
on except always explicit the kind of exception and use getLogger to log the exception

###example
        try:
            return self.i2c_bus.read_byte_data(0x69, 0x00) == 0x11
        except (OSError, IOError) as e:
            getLogger().warning("Error reading WittyPi: %s", e)

## Coding standard

### Try to follow the DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) principle to avoid code duplication
### The coding style should comply with Black formatter https://black.readthedocs.io/en/stable/
### Run Black (inside the .venv directory) to check the style
### Delete trailing whitespaces
### Imports must be at the beginning of the source file
### System imports must be declared before project imports


